                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1121">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">814.00/1476: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Guatemala</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Long</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Guatemala</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-06-25T00:00:00-06:00"
                            >June 25, 1944—midnight</date>.<lb/>[Received June 26—1:03
                        p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>409. Renewed negotiations this afternoon by delegation referred to in my
                    telegrams of today attended by President and part of Cabinet resulted in
                    deadlock. I will accompany committee from Diplomatic Corps tomorrow morning to
                    inform the Minister for Foreign Affairs<note n="4" xml:id="d1121fn4">Carlos
                        Salazar.</note> that we consider our mission accomplished, expressing regret
                    at lack of success and lamenting shooting incident this evening during exercise
                    of good offices by Corps. We will also express hope on humanitarian grounds that
                    practical armistice may be instituted by withdrawal of troops from streets.
                    While situation is not quite hopeless, <hi rend="italic">intransigeant</hi>
                    attitude of Government and today’s ruthless policy measures are distinctly
                    discouraging developments. Corps will endeavor to keep door open for possible
                    renewal of negotiations.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Long</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
